📘 Situation

You are the on-call DevOps engineer responsible for maintaining a production environment.

At 02:00 AM, an alert is triggered indicating that the production API service is unreachable.

You immediately connect to Server 3 to investigate the issue. Initial checks suggest that the application might not be running inside its Docker container.

🧩 Your Responsibilities

Based on the operational guidelines, you must:

🔍 1. Investigation
Verify whether the application container is currently running.
Identify any container that has stopped unexpectedly.
Examine the logs of the failed container to determine the root cause.
(Hint: Look for memory-related termination messages such as OOM-related errors.)
🛠️ 2. Service Restoration
Start a new container instance to restore the application.
Ensure that the container is launched using the exact production configuration:
Parameter	Value
Container Name	api-container
Image	myapp:v2.1.3
Restart Policy	unless-stopped
Port Mapping	8080:8080
Mode	Detached
📍 Working Directory
/home/user
✅ Expected Result
A new container named api-container is successfully running.
The application is accessible via port 8080.
The root cause of the failure is identified from logs.

